# Defect Log

Record visual or workflow defects that gates missed. Keep this file readable by
future agents; fix encoding problems before adding screenshots or comments.

## Defect Template

### D-001: <short title>

- Status: open | fixed | verified | wontfix
- Page/route:
- Figma reference:
- Implementation screenshot:
- Root cause:
- Fix plan:
- Verification:
- Harness follow-up:

## G1 Failure Categories

Use these categories when strict visual regression reports them:

- `required-anchor-missing`: add exact `data-anchor` values from the manifest.
- `decorative-flow-drift`: move visible decor from normal flow to a root/page
  decor layer.
- `media-position-drift`: size or place a primary image/media element from its
  manifest bbox.
- `control-text-anchor-mismatch`: separate outer control anchors from inner text
  label anchors.
- `footer-wordmark-target`: attach the anchor to the full-size wordmark element.
- `repeated-stack-height-drift`: align repeated exhibit/card image heights to
  manifest bbox ratios.
- `repeated-logo-scale-drift`: normalize repeated brand/logo card media to the
  Figma bbox or optical-size metadata.
- `section-height-explosion`: reduce padding/stacking so the section bbox
  matches Figma.
- `text-metric-mismatch`: fix font loading, font-size, line-height, or text
  anchor target.

## Common Visual Defects To Check

### Decorative Layering

- Decorative images must not cover text, nav, cards, or footer content.
- Decorative assets should use `pointer-events: none`.
- Prefer a dedicated decor layer in layout components.
- Content layers such as header/main/footer should have explicit stacking order.
- If the Figma asset overlaps nav/main or has negative y, it belongs in a
  root/page decor layer rather than normal flow.

### Anchor Targeting

- Required anchors from `baselines/<Page>/anchors-*.json` must exist exactly in
  the DOM.
- Nav/button controls often need separate anchors for the outer frame and inner
  text label.
- Footer brand anchors should be on the full-size wordmark, not an inner span.

### Repeated Image Stacks

- Case-study/exhibit images should follow manifest bbox order and height.
- Avoid `height:auto` when natural image ratio causes cumulative y drift.
- If later repeated anchors drift more than earlier ones, check per-item height
  and gap accumulation.

### Logo And Icon Normalization

- Logos with different viewBox/whitespace need per-asset normalization.
- Use metadata such as `logoScale`, `logoClassName`, `logoFit`, or CSS variables
  like `--logo-scale`.
- Put repeated logos in a deliberate fit box and render the mark with
  `object-fit: contain`.
- Avoid relying only on `width: 100%; height: auto`; natural asset ratios often
  make repeated brand cards look optically inconsistent.
- Compare optical size against Figma, not only CSS box size.

### Hug-Content Controls

- Pills, chips, tags, badges, and small labels should match Figma hug-content
  sizing.
- Use `inline-flex`, `width: fit-content`, `white-space: nowrap`, and
  `justify-self`/`align-self: start`.
- Do not allow label controls to stretch to the parent grid/flex column unless
  the Figma node is explicitly full width.

### Text Encoding

- Fix mojibake before verification.
- Treat broken strings in React/data files as implementation defects.
